<font color="#FF0000">PTSD</font><br>
<tt>Wed Sep 17 19:55:41 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Symptoms:  Disturbed sleep patterns.   Over control of emotions.   Intrusive thoughts.  Heightened sensitivity to loud noises.  Psychic numbing.   Uncontrolled rage.  Many others that I have forgotten.  <br>
Two hours up and two hours down.  I never slept a full eight hours for twenty years.  Thought it was normal to get up, patrol the perimeter and then go back to bed.<br>
Never cry=out of control.  Never love=out of control<br>
Never laugh= out of control.  I learned that control is a funny  thing , it winds up that you are controlled.  My wife (then) of 20 years never saw tears in my eyes. Control!!  I discovered that if one has that much control, there is a consequence=Stress!<br>
Intrusive thoughts! Always and I mean always relating conversations to experiences learned in Vietnam.  Every thing that is seen, heard, touched, tasted is in some way related to Vietnam.  Daydreams about Vietnam,Nite dreams about Vietnam.<br>
So in control of emotions that when you do go off.  You explode!  No gradual rise from anger to mad to rage.  I'm talking RAGE!  Piss me off and suffer the consequences.  Not that I was bad, just didn't know how to get angry.  Lots of fights with anybody, everybody.  Biggest, baddest m-f in the valley.  RAGE!  God, did it feel good!  Lock and load!  Rock and roll!  <br>
Just a little bit of my PTSD.    
